If what he and his cohorts tried to do to stop the ANC from losing votes in 2016 was above board, why did they agree to pay R1-million to a whistle-blower? And if he did no wrong, why is he avoiding answering journalists' questions? His only claim to fame is being a Sisulu. But now he will go down in history as the first Sisulu to be involved in a corrupt bid to stifle democracy.